The paper focuses on defining and conceptualizing actionable insight in data analytics, which involves aspects of human-computer interaction (HC) and database systems (DB). The proposed conceptual framework also incorporates artificial intelligence (AI) and information retrieval (IR) techniques. Additionally, the paper discusses the computational and analytical requirements for each component of actionable insight, which falls under the category of machine learning (LG).
